The paper introduces a deep generative model for machine learning on graph-structured data, specifically for spatio-temporal solar irradiance forecasting. This involves the use of convolutional graph auto-encoder (CGAE), which combines techniques from deep learning, spectral graph convolutions, and variational Bayesian inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also involves the use of neural architecture, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and probabilistic modeling, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
